# Army builder — game data (`projects/army-builder/data/`)

Static reference data shipped with the site. **Not** user saves — those belong in localStorage.

## Files

- `catalog.json` — eras, army ids, and `file` pointers to army JSON
- `armies/<id>.json` — unit profiles for one army sheet

## Adding a new army sheet

1. Create `armies/<id>.json` matching existing schema (`id`, `name`, `era`, `units[]`, etc.)
2. Register it in `catalog.json` under the correct era
3. Army `id` should match the filename (without `.json`)

## Unit profile fields (typical)

`id`, `name`, `type` (infantry|cavalry|artillery), `figuresMin`, `figuresMax`, `weapon`, `rangeInches`, `fire`, `melee`, `tenacity`, `specialRules`, `points`

## Data integrity

- Stats and points must match official Perry Valour & Fortitude army sheets
- Keep `sheetVersion` and `sourceUrl` accurate on army JSON files
- `netlify.toml` serves data at `/api/catalog` and `/api/army/:id`

